Exporters / Components Explained:

1) Prometheus (Metrics Collector)
 
    ->Scrapes metrics from targets on a schedule.
    ->Stores metrics in time-series database.

2) Grafana (Visualization)

    ->Reads metrics from Prometheus.
    ->Reads logs from Loki.
    ->Builds dashboards, alerts.

3) Node Exporter (Server Metrics, Gives server-level metrics):

    ->CPU usage
    ->RAM usage
    ->Disk usage
    ->Load average
    ->Network I/O
    ->Filesystem stats

4) cAdvisor (Container Metrics, Gives Docker/container-level metrics)

    ->CPU per container
    ->Memory per container
    ->Network per container
    ->Filesystem per container
Note: cAdvisor is for metrics, not logs.

5) Blackbox Exporter (Uptime / Endpoint Monitoring)

    ->Website HTTP/HTTPS status (200 OK)
    ->SSL/TLS availability
    ->DNS query success (optional)
    ->Response time

6) Loki (Log Storage)

    ->Stores logs like a database.

7) Promtail (Log Shipper)

Reads logs from:
    ->/var/log/syslog, /var/log/auth.log
    ->Nginx logs: /var/log/nginx/*.log
    ->Docker container logs: /var/lib/docker/containers/*/*.log
      Then pushes to Loki.

